---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About | Growth Map"
  description="I'm an operator who earned his battle scars by doing the work. Growth Map helps founders build the systems that make growth predictable."
  canonicalPath="/about"
>
  <!-- HERO / INTRO -->
  <section class="bg-white px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto flex max-w-[1200px] flex-col items-center gap-12 md:flex-row md:gap-16">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-bright-blue">
          About me
        </p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold leading-tight text-navy sm:text-4xl md:text-[48px] md:leading-[1.1]">
          The Story Behind Growth Map
        </h1>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-shrink-0">
        <img
          src="/images/about-photo.jpeg"
          alt="Cameron Oliver"
          class="w-72 rounded-2xl shadow-lg md:w-96"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STORY -->
  <section class="bg-light-gray px-6 py-20 md:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] space-y-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-dark-text">
      <p>
        I've spent the past decade inside fast-growing startups — from employee #3 to 100+ and back — usually as the person leaders call when things start breaking.
      </p>
      <p>
        My work has always sat in the middle of operations, go-to-market, delivery, and product… translating vision into the systems, roles, and rhythms that make a company work.
      </p>
      <p>
        After enough years in the trenches, the same pattern became impossible to ignore.
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-4 pl-1">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-2 w-2 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-bright-blue"></span>
          Founders were overwhelmed.
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-2 w-2 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-bright-blue"></span>
          Teams were misaligned.
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-2 w-2 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-bright-blue"></span>
          Everyone was working hard, but without a shared understanding of how the business actually created value.
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-2 w-2 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-bright-blue"></span>
          That gap led to bad hires, unclear priorities, chaotic execution, and a constant feeling of running the company on instinct instead of insight.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        I didn't build Growth Map because I wanted a consulting practice. I built it because I was tired of watching good companies waste potential — and tired of watching founders carry the anxiety that comes with that.
      </p>
      <p>
        My background taught me how quickly a team drifts without role clarity, how much money gets burned on the wrong hires, and how stressful it becomes when a founder tries to hold the entire business together themselves. I've lived inside messy, high-pressure environments, responsible for making complex initiatives land.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm not a theorist. I'm not a career consultant. I'm an operator who earned his battle scars by doing the work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Growth Map is my way of giving founders what I always wished we had in every company I operated:
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-4 pl-1">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-2 w-2 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-bright-blue"></span>
          A clear picture of how the business works
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-2 w-2 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-bright-blue"></span>
          A sense of what actually drives outcomes
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-2 w-2 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-bright-blue"></span>
          A practical way to make decisions week to week
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span class="mt-1.5 h-2 w-2 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-bright-blue"></span>
          And a path to grow without chaos
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        If you want a business that makes sense, a team that moves in sync, and growth that doesn't depend on burnout, you're in the right place.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
